Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.67,0:00:02.84,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Suspense and deduction closes the gap between
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.84,0:00:04.61,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the love and hatred between two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.61,0:00:06.41,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Watching soccer evokes different memories
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.41,0:00:08.65,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}they all coalesce to solve a mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.65,0:00:10.28,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees through the one and only truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.28,0:00:12.38,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a child in appearance with the I.Q. of an adult
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.38,0:00:14.42,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}no case is left unsolved with Detective Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.36,0:01:48.70,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We, the Detective Boys, went with Dr. Agasa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.70,0:01:50.70,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}to watch a soccer game for the first time in ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.62,0:02:05.59,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The match was won by our team, the Tōkyō Spirits,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.59,0:02:09.46,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}who defeated Noir Tōkyō, winning the Tōkyō Derby.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.51,0:02:16.30,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The train on the way back was packed with supporters for both teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.10,0:02:25.02,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But when the passengers left,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.02,0:02:28.28,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a man's body was found, having been murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.28,0:02:29.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.82,0:02:32.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't move this train!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.32,0:02:34.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man's been stabbed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.41,0:02:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, please call the ticket control barriers connected to this platform,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.70,0:02:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and ask them to check all the tickets from Tokyo Spirits and Noir Tokyo supporters trying to leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.21,0:02:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop anyone who has a ticket bought before 5 PM from leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.34,0:02:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.38,0:02:59.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just do it! If you don't, the killer might get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.63,0:03:05.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The victim was a fanatic supporter of Noir Tōkyō,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.05,0:03:11.52,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a proud hooligan who often appeared in the news and TV due to the crimes he committed:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.52,0:03:13.27,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kadotake Akano{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.90,0:03:21.41,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There were three suspects: Hasue Kira{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.20,0:03:24.41,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Mitsuaki Funato{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.12,0:03:27.41,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and Etsutoshi Ōba{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.83,0:03:41.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The only thing we know for sure is that they all rode in a packed train car.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.43,0:03:47.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But that's not enough to conclude anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.31,0:03:51.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's gotta be something... There's gotta be something more!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.23,0:03:54.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Some other clue to solve the case!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.54,0:04:15.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Though...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.12,0:04:17.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How come that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.58,0:04:18.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.29,0:04:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.01,0:04:22.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, where's Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.83,0:04:25.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she was going to the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.32,0:04:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, how's the match going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.24,0:04:30.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were following it through the radio, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.66,0:04:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.71,0:04:36.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the congestion when getting off the train, I think I dropped the radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.24,0:04:39.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I can't find it on the train, nor on the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.16,0:04:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man, you're such a klutz.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.75,0:04:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure someone must've found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.83,0:04:53.42,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We're still 0-0, and the match is now entering injury time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.42,0:04:56.74,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh! Ramus made a splendid pass to the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.74,0:05:00.45,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Higo got the ball, and the defenders can't keep up with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.45,0:05:05.37,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's a decisive moment!\NHigo goes straight for the goal!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.37,0:05:10.58,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Now one-on-one in front of the goal, Higo shoots!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.58,0:05:13.25,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ahh, he hit the goal post!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.25,0:05:17.45,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Have even the heavens themselves abandoned Higo?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.45,0:05:20.91,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Even so, there's an enormous booing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.50,0:05:29.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} remind you of someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.42,0:05:32.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Noir{\i0} is French for {\i1}black{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.59,0:05:36.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A traitor who abandoned black.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.88,0:05:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.10,0:05:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though, Haibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.65,0:05:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had a reason to leave his team, just like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.10,0:05:48.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has an older brother from a different mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.95,0:05:51.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name's Rikuo Endō.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.04,0:05:55.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a substitute defender in the J-League for Noir until last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.45,0:05:58.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, this isn't widely known information,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.12,0:06:02.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since they have different last names, and they've kept it a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.54,0:06:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found out about it two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.74,0:06:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when I was in a match during my third year of middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.12,0:06:12.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and his brother, who'd just signed up for Noir, had come to see the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.01,0:06:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said something to me that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.22,0:06:23.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Would you like to join Noir Tokyo too, and reach the top with us brothers?" {sounds awkward as fuck, but I can't word this decently to save my life}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.59,0:06:34.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, this year, Noir Tokyo told Endō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} he wasn't allowed to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.84,0:06:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the reason they let Endō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who didn't even stand out in J-2 into the team...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.30,0:06:44.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...was merely as bait to lure Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.63,0:06:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon learning of this, Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.93,0:06:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,signed up for Big Ōsaka, who'd hired the retired Endō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as a coach,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.00,0:06:57.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in order to fulfill their dream of winning the J-1 together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.47,0:07:01.93,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Higo was knocked down!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.93,0:07:04.63,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This should be a yellow card...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.63,0:07:07.34,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the referee doesn't show a card!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.34,0:07:11.30,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And even though their forward just suffered a foul...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.30,0:07:13.68,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Listen to the audience's cheering.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.26,0:07:17.76,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Has Higo been forsaken by all who supported him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.76,0:07:23.22,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is there no field in Japan where Higo can play?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.82,0:07:26.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.44,0:07:29.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If I recall correctly, today's Tōkyō Derby was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.76,0:07:33.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.51,0:07:36.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The killer is the one who lied!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.09,0:07:41.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Furthermore, if my reasoning is correct, the killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.64,0:07:43.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}...should still have the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.65,0:07:59.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.57,0:08:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The train car where the crime took place has been moved to the garage...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.23,0:08:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we're almost done inspecting the entrances and exits of the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.11,0:08:13.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we've done all we can at this station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.73,0:08:14.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All that's left...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.98,0:08:18.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...is to invite you three suspects over,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.48,0:08:20.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we can record your stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.82,0:08:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on! That's voluntary, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.86,0:08:27.98,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Hasue Kira (24)\NNoir Tōkyō Supporter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.86,0:08:27.98,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mitsuaki Funato (33)\NTōkyō Spirits Supporter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.73,0:08:29.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gimme a break! I've got to get back to work quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.19,0:08:32.78,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Etsutoshi Ōba (29)\NNoir Tōkyō Supporter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.19,0:08:32.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, couldn't we do this some other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.19,0:08:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.15,0:08:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we wait too long, the definitive evidence will disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.95,0:08:49.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or do you have a concrete reason why you need to leave the murder scene as soon as possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.07,0:08:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.15,0:08:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that, old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.77,0:08:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't talk like you're a detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.92,0:09:00.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that you figured out who the killer is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.09,0:09:01.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.47,0:09:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course. It became clear when I heard the three's stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.59,0:09:10.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer is the lying fake supporter!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.31,0:09:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.72,0:09:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fake supporter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.55,0:09:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.22,0:09:17.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's this guy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.27,0:09:18.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.28,0:09:23.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I remember you saying that you missed seeing the two wingers score the winning goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.99,0:09:26.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.32,0:09:29.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Hide-Naoki combo scored the winning goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.49,0:09:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're forwards who move freely through the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.29,0:09:36.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're not wingers, whose main job is to stay in the lines and recover the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.74,0:09:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.66,0:09:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.45,0:09:43.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, wingers are part of an old game tactic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.44,0:09:46.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not really used in soccer nowadays.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.57,0:09:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, I've only been a soccer fan for a short time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.24,0:09:57.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I thought I remembered someone saying Hide and Naoki were really good wingers...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.57,0:10:00.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop playing dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.20,0:10:02.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the killer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.08,0:10:03.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.74,0:10:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just an honest mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.27,0:10:06.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.64,0:10:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Referring to them as "wingers" is a mistake, but not a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.77,0:10:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.43,0:10:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about the person who didn't watch the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.06,0:10:22.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but who acted otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.77,0:10:25.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.22,0:10:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today's match was the Tokyo Derby, between the two greatest teams in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.86,0:10:33.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stadium was packed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.19,0:10:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the killer had watched the game along with Akano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was at the stands,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.27,0:10:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he would surely have lost sight of him among the crowd after the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.56,0:10:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then where did the killer wait for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.02,0:10:51.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably inside the stadium's toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.56,0:10:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He listened to the match on the radio, and as soon as the match was over,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.81,0:10:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he probably hurried over to the exit, and waited there for Akano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.98,0:11:04.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who's this lying killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.50,0:11:10.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I ask them some questions, to verify if they really {\i1}did{\i0} watch the game or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.47,0:11:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I watched the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.18,0:11:15.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw Naoki's shot from the front stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.21,0:11:21.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was so annoyed with his shot that I ended up arguing with a nearby Spirits supporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.43,0:11:26.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw it too, from Noir's supporters' stand behind the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.59,0:11:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hide dribbled past all the defenders, and in front of the goal, he passed the ball to Naoki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.38,0:11:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was watching it from the Spirits' stand behind the opposite goal, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.76,0:11:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got that call from work, so I wasn't able to see the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.79,0:11:49.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you {\i1}did{\i0} know that it was Hide and Naoki who scored the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.22,0:11:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obviously!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.09,0:11:56.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the goal, the supporters around me cheered "Hide and Naoki are the greatest!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.80,0:12:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think I'm lying, have a look at my ticket stub, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.01,0:12:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got mine too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.97,0:12:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got mine too, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.31,0:12:09.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.22,0:12:14.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For people who didn't watch the match, my explanation might be hard to understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.14,0:12:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to ask these kids who watched the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.60,0:12:19.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were our seats?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.97,0:12:22.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The front stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.10,0:12:25.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's right in the middle, so we could clearly see Hide dribble past four players.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:30.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though we didn't see this lady in the front stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.81,0:12:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe my seat was away from yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.26,0:12:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoa, wait. You can't think I'm a liar over just this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.97,0:12:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. It's not like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.60,0:12:47.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then from what side and which way did Hide cross while dribbling past the four players?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.22,0:12:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From right to left!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.07,0:12:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then from your point of view, the Noir goal was to your left, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.77,0:12:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, what about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.61,0:12:59.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't remember until I saw my own ticket, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.36,0:13:03.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today's Tokyo Derby took place in the Spirits' stadium, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.11,0:13:07.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usually, in the J-League,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.20,0:13:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if you look from the front stand, the home team's supporters sit behind the left goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.37,0:13:18.57,Signs,,0,0,0,,Front stand
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.37,0:13:18.57,Signs,,0,0,0,,Away
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.37,0:13:18.57,Signs,,0,0,0,,Home
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.95,0:13:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,whereas the away team's supporters sit behind the right goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.57,0:13:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning that in today's match, the Tokyo Spirits' seats were on the left,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.78,0:13:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,whereas Noir Tokyo's were on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.57,0:13:31.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now you see what I mean, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.62,0:13:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The strange contradiction that the lying killer doesn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.28,0:13:47.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange contradiction?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.58,0:13:51.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you explain it a bit more clearly?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.66,0:13:52.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.87,0:13:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I was saying earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.61,0:13:57.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you look from the front stand...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.24,0:13:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Tokyo Spirits were to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.41,0:14:07.40,Signs,,0,0,0,,Noir Tokyo
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.41,0:14:07.40,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tokyo Spirits
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.41,0:14:07.40,Signs,,0,0,0,,Front stand
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.83,0:14:03.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the Noir Tokyo supporters were to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.32,0:14:06.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hide dribbled the ball from right to left,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.70,0:14:09.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Naoki, who received Hide's pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.04,0:14:11.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,scored in the left-side goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.61,0:14:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right in front of the Spirits' supporters.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.41,0:14:18.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.37,0:14:24.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way you would have said that Hide dribbled past the defenders and "approached"...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.57,0:14:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...if you were sitting in Noir Tokyo's seats on the right side, Ōba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.00,0:14:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, you interpreted what you heard over the radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.99,0:14:39.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Hide's approaching the goal!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.73,0:14:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's just wordplay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.85,0:14:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like him, I just made a mistake. I'm not lying...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.19,0:14:52.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I meant that Hide was approaching the opposite goal!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.07,0:14:54.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just said it wrong because I was nervous!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.10,0:14:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want, you can check the seat on my ticket!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.31,0:15:00.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll see I was sitting in Noir's seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.27,0:15:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, you weren't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.92,0:15:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.76,0:15:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's completely impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.14,0:15:09.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not if you were dressed like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.01,0:15:13.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold on. That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.67,0:15:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo's shirt, the one who betrayed Noir!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.14,0:15:21.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'd gone to Noir's seats dressed like that, you'd have gotten lynched!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.43,0:15:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That said, Agasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.26,0:15:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,this is all circumstancial evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.97,0:15:31.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need definitive evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.84,0:15:35.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He should still have the evidence in his arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.42,0:15:40.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the watch mark in his right arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.01,0:15:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All that proves is that he had his arms crossed in that crowded train.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.76,0:15:46.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean his other arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.52,0:15:48.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His other arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.55,0:15:51.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.47,0:15:55.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he pulled a knife out of his bag in a packed train,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.72,0:15:58.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he would've looked suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.30,0:16:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, Ōba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had his arms crossed while holding the knife,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.46,0:16:05.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,therefore ensuring nobody could see it,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.84,0:16:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as well as allowing him to pull the knife out at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.93,0:16:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, he had a glove in the hand holding the knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.70,0:16:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. And if my reasoning is correct, there should still be something on his left arm. {literally "on his other, non-dominant arm." but seriously, just no.}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.62,0:16:29.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After holding it for so long, the rare design on the knife's scabbard must've left a mark!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.99,0:16:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.20,0:16:33.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then... it was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.61,0:16:37.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For my brother's sake...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.32,0:16:41.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I studied soccer, became a supporter,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.12,0:16:43.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and came up with this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.70,0:16:47.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who'd have known he was the one causing me to fail?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.93,0:16:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.93,0:16:52.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My twin brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.67,0:16:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A year ago, Akano killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.56,0:16:58.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.81,0:17:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that day, a year ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.02,0:17:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My brother came home from watching a Noir Tokyo match...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.23,0:17:07.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,covered in injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.73,0:17:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he'd fallen down the stairs in the stadium.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.73,0:17:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that night, he suddenly fell to the ground holding his head,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.67,0:17:17.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and lost consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.52,0:17:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He died three days later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.22,0:17:25.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His death was caused by a brain hemorrhage from a crack to his skull.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.01,0:17:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found out what really happened when I went to the Tokyo Hooligan site that my brother used to visit,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.96,0:17:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akano's homepage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.80,0:17:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understood everything after I read his comments for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.44,0:17:40.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today, after the match, I beat the crap out of a moron who criticized my homepage,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.82,0:17:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and threw him down the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.98,0:17:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what he wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.02,0:17:50.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know that was your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.73,0:17:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.27,0:17:56.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I met Akano to be sure of what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.14,0:18:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he saw at my face and said, grinning...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.15,0:18:05.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"So you're still alive?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.73,0:18:09.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I decided to avenge my brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.90,0:18:12.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with his most prized possessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.14,0:18:14.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then that uniform...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.55,0:18:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. My brother always wore it to Noir games...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.39,0:18:21.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo's uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.89,0:18:24.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never imagined I would get caught over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.22,0:18:30.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though, maybe this uniform was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.39,0:18:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a warning from my brother in the afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.18,0:18:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if a Noir supporter had seen this uniform and commented about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.05,0:18:51.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it would've brought me to my senses from the thirst for revenge in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.48,0:18:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"What do you think you're doing?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:08.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Haibara's taking a long time...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.70,0:19:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.95,0:19:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Haibara's not back yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.03,0:19:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.28,0:19:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! There she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.24,0:19:18.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! On the other platform!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.70,0:19:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.16,0:19:23.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's she doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.61,0:19:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The train to Beika's on {\i1}this{\i0} platform...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.58,0:19:31.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me she's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.65,0:19:36.37,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}After all, there's no place for traitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.66,0:19:43.99,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's his chance to forget everything and escape to a place where the booing won't reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.28,0:19:46.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.66,0:20:20.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara...{Puto had this as thoughts}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.12,0:20:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.02,0:21:53.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara...{Puto had this as thoughts}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.18,0:21:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.44,0:22:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.86,0:22:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's all the yelling for?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.06,0:22:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought I was going to run or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.77,0:22:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.81,0:22:15.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go, young lady. Try not to drop it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.44,0:22:17.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.27,0:22:18.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A radio?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.17,0:22:21.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was looking for the radio that Tsuburaya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.02,0:22:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I asked a worker, he told me one of the cleaners might've picked it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.98,0:22:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.29,0:22:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.67,0:22:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Don't run away. Don't run away from fate."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.14,0:22:47.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll protect me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.07,0:22:49.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.07,0:23:00.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not some weak girl who needs to be protected all the time like you seem to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.98,0:23:04.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.68,0:23:07.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Higo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did manage to score the winning goal in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.53,0:23:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stadium went wild calling for Higo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.81,0:23:21.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though I pretty much knew it already, but that booing was the motivation he needed to give it his all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.77,0:23:26.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you telling me all of that nonsense?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.23,0:23:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not some soccer nut like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.98,0:23:44.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Man, she's stubborn...
